TKASLICE  LLLLLLLLLLLLUUUUUUUUUUUU CCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCC
TKASLICE:  Verb to add a slice display on TEK from slice file
INNAME                             Image name (name)
INCLASS                            Image name (class)
INSEQ           0.0      9999.0    Image name (seq. #)
INDISK          0.0         9.0    Disk drive #
INVERS          0.0     46655.0    Version # of SL file. 0=>last
PIXRANGE                           Min,Max of image intensity
                                     0 => entire range
BDROP           0.0      9999.0    Drop slice pts from beginning
EDROP           0.0      9999.0    Drop slice pts from end
----------------------------------------------------------------
TKASLICE
Type: Verb
Use:  TKASLICE will add further displays from a SL file
      directly on a TEK 4012 device.  This verb should be used
      after TKSLICE has initiated the plot.
Adverbs:
  INNAME......Image name (name).          Standard defaults.
  INCLASS.....Image name (class).         Standard defaults.
  INSEQ.......Image name (seq. #).        0 => highest.
  INDISK......Disk unit #.                0 => any.
  INVERS......Version # of SL file.       0 => highest version #
  PIXRANGE....Min,Max of Image intensity. 0,0 => image min, max.
  BDROP.......No of slice pts to omit from beginning of plot.
  EDROP.......No of slice points to omit from end of plot.
----------------------------------------------------------------
